						Presently afterwards the ancient matron, together with her son, sat down on
						seats before prepared, and commanded the redeemed should be told. Now as
						soon as she had demanded everyone's name, which were also written down by a
						little page; having viewed us all, one after another, she sighed, and spoke
						to her son, so that I could well hear her, "Ah, how heartily I am grieved
						for the poor men in the dungeon! I would to God I could release them all."
