					Chapter 2: Section 5: Paragraph 4
				-
					-
						To this I now made great haste, and reached it in so much daylight as to
						take a very competent view of it. Now it was an exceedingly royal beautiful
						portal, on which were carved a multitude of most noble figures and devices,
						every one of which (as I afterwards learned) had its peculiar
						signification. Above was fixed a pretty large tablet, with these words,
						"Procul hinc, procul ite profani" ("keep away, you who are profane"), and
						other things more, that I was earnestly forbidden to relate.
					-
