						and excellent a manner, that it made the very heart in my body rejoice.
						However, certain great Sr John's made but little reckoning of them, but
						jeered and winked at one another, biting their lips within their hats, and
						using other similar unseemly gestures. After this, meat was brought in, and
						although no one could be seen, yet everything was so orderly managed, that
						it seemed to me as if every guest had his own attendant. Now my artists
						having somewhat recreated themselves, and the wine having removed a little
