						Now as soon as the lovely day was broken, and the bright Sun, having raised
						himself above the hills, had again took himself to his appointed office in
						the high Heaven, my good champions began to rise out of their beds, and
						leisurely to make themselves ready for the Inquisition. Whereupon, one
						after another, they came again into the hall, and saying good morning,
						demanded how we had slept that night; and having seen our bonds, there were
						some that reproved us for being so cowardly, and because we had not,
						rather, like them, hazarded upon all adventures. However, some of them
						whose hearts still smote them made no loud cry of the business. We excused
						ourselves with our ignorance, hoping we should now soon be set at liberty,
						and learn wisdom by this disgrace, that they on the contrary had not yet
						altogether escaped; and perhaps their greatest danger was still to come.
					-
