						this was a white serpent, who was of such a length that though she wound
						about the rest of it in a circle, her tail still remained in one of the
						eyeholes until her head again entered the other; so she never stirred from
						her skull, unless it happened that Cupid twitched a little at her, for then
						she slipped in so suddenly that we all could not choose but marvel at it.
