						House of the Sun, there next to the King and Queen, upon a richly furnished
						scaffold, to behold the previously ordained comedy. We indeed, though
						separated, stood on the right hand of the Kings, but the virgins stood on
						the left, except those to whom the Royal Ensigns were committed. To them
						was allotted their own place at the top of all. But the rest of the
