					-
						With this she intimated that we should go to sleep, and trouble ourselves
						no further on their part, for they should be sure to have their due right.
						And so she bade us all goodnight, saying that she must watch the dead
						bodies this night. We did this, and were each of us conducted by our pages
						into our lodgings. My page talked with me of sundry and various matters
						(which I still remember very well) and gave me cause enough to admire his
						understanding. But his intention was to lull me to sleep, which at last I
						well observed; so I made as though I was fast asleep, but no sleep came
						into my eyes, and I could not put the beheaded out of my mind.
					-
