						Then I saw a rich bed ready made, hung about with curious curtains, one of
						which he drew aside, where I saw the Lady Venus stark naked (for he heaved
						up the coverlets too) lying there in such beauty, and in such a surprising
						fashion, that I was almost beside myself; neither do I yet know whether it
						was a piece thus carved, or a human corpse that lay dead there. For she was
						altogether immovable, and yet I dared not touch her. So she was again
						covered, and the curtain drawn before her, yet she was still (as it were)
						in my eye. But I soon saw behind the bed a tablet on which it was written
						as follows:
