						I asked my page about this writing, but he laughed, with the promise that I
						should know it too. So, he putting out the torch, we ascended again. Then I
						had a better look at all the little doors, and first found that on every
						corner there burned a small taper of pyrites, of which I had before taken
						no notice, for the fire was so clear that it looked much more like a stone
						than a taper. From this heat the tree was forced continually to melt, yet
						it still produced new fruit. Now behold (said the page) what I heard
						revealed to the King by Atlas. When the tree (he said) shall be quite
						melted down, then shall Lady Venus awake, and be the mother of a King.
					-
