						Whilst he was thus speaking, in flew the little Cupid, who at first was
						somewhat abashed at our presence, but seeing us both look more like the
						dead than the living, he could not in the end refrain from laughing,
						demanding what spirit had brought us there. I with trembling answered him,
						that I had lost my way in the castle, and had come here by chance, and that
						the page likewise had been looking up and down for me, and at last came
