						First stood the Virgin A with her attendants in a ring round about with the
						lamps and branches C. Next stood we with our torches B, then the musicians
						A in a long rank; last of all the rest of the virgins D in another long
						rank too. Now where the virgins came from, whether they lived in the
						castle, or whether they had been brought in by night, I do not know, for
						all their faces were covered with delicate white linen, so that I could not
						recognise any of them.
					-
				-
